The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance and State's motion, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of Judgment of Conviction.

  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

 Court sentenced defendant to serve 7 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 7 days served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 11/28/2016, or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept. Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable. If all costs fees and surcharges are paid the defendant is eligible for expungment.

Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  

As a condition of bail, court order the defendant may not possess dangerous weapons or firearms or apply for a conceal carry permit.
